{"body": "I'd like to understand the motivations behind moving this out of rails core. I had a brief exchange with @steveklabnik and understand that maybe developers should just be using Rack::Cache/Varnish + proper HTTP caching headers, but action caching also allows you hit your middleware and filter stack, which is useful for authentication.\r\n\r\nI'm all for moving page caching out though, as it bypasses the Rails stack altogether.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9118566", "created_at": "2012-10-03T19:17:50Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7833#issuecomment-9118566", "updated_at": "2012-10-03T19:17:50Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7833, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/andrewle", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/7ea103436529e692f0385d284b3d2e9d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fb47f138d4e501c7d2b1be8149fdadd35.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/received_events", "gravatar_id": "7ea103436529e692f0385d284b3d2e9d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "andrewle", "type": "User", "id": 95214, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrewle/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f881bd3543c15100b2c8"}, "id": 9118566, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7833"}
